<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEE483929FAF889FB6BBB59" blockId="4.[166,1225,1802,1861]" lastBlockId="5.[174,1233,175,874]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="412" pageId="4" pageNumber="411">
D e s c r i p t i o n. Head (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEE483828D3F889FDD1BD56" box="[498,618,1802,1829]" captionStart="Figs 30–38" captionStartId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-306@5.[267,1169,874,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 30–38. M. pratensis sp. n., holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="411">
fig. 30 
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEE48382B1DF889FDF0BD57" bold="true" box="[572,587,1802,1828]" pageId="4" pageNumber="411">–</emphasis>
31
</figureCitation>
). Orbit projected above eye in profile only at level of orb s; 3 orb s, 3 fr s; frorb sta elongated in several rows, reclinate nearest to eye and proclinate nearest to frons; orbit wide and shining (frontal view); frontal carina absent; lunule slightly shining, high, rounded dorsally, with deep furrow; ocellar triangle as matt as frons, wide, with distinct contours; vibrissa and sbvb s are of the same length; maximum high of eye 4.8× as maximum high of gena; gena slightly acute ventrally; 1st flagellomere rounded (lateral view).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEF483929C3FEACFB95BBF9" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">
Wing (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEF48392815FEACFE3BBB39" box="[308,384,303,330]" captionStart="Figs 30–38" captionStartId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-306@5.[267,1169,874,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 30–38. M. pratensis sp. n., holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">fig. 34</figureCitation>
) slightly yellowish, with all veins brown; costa reaching M 
<subScript id="178C34F3FFEF48392D17FEC1FB85BB23" attach="left" box="[1078,1086,322,336]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">1</subScript>
; last section of CuA 
<subScript id="178C34F3FFEF48392824FEE1FEB6BB03" attach="left" box="[261,269,354,368]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">1</subScript>
0.85× as long as penultimate; costal sections 
<quantity id="4CF09B53FFEF48392A08FECCFCCFBB19" box="[809,884,335,362]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="5.08" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" unit="in" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 in</quantity>
the ratio of 3.87: 1.06: 1.00; calypter and fringe white, margin yellow. Wing length 
<quantity id="4CF09B53FFEF48392A0EFEECFC33BBF9" box="[815,904,367,394]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
in both sexes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEF483929C3FE0CFECABB99" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">Mesonotum and scutellum slightly shining, blackish-grey (dorsal view); abdomen strongly shining, yellowish-green; 2 dc; ac in 8 irregular rows at level of 2nd dc; halters and legs dark brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEF483929C3FE6CFB35B8F9" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">
Male terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEF48392891FE6CFD33B879" box="[432,648,495,522]" captionStart="Figs 30–38" captionStartId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-306@5.[267,1169,874,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 30–38. M. pratensis sp. n., holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">figs 32, 33, 35, 36</figureCitation>
). Epandrium covered with long hairs; inner surface of surstylus covered only with numerous short and small prensisetae; hypandrium V-shaped, with obtuse apex (ventral view); ejaculatory apodeme slightly longer than phallus; phallus 
<quantity id="4CF09B53FFEF48392818FDCCFE1BB819" box="[313,416,591,618]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" unit="mm" value="0.21">0.21 mm</quantity>
long; distiphallus complex elongated, oval and narrowing posteriorly (ventral view); mesophallus long, flattened apically; basiphallus typical for the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEF483929C3FD0CFE9AB959" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">
Female terminalia (
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEF483928E7FD0CFDF8B8D9" box="[454,579,655,682]" captionStart="Figs 30–38" captionStartId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-306@5.[267,1169,874,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 30–38. M. pratensis sp. n., holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">
figs 37 
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEF48392B35FD0CFD98B8DA" bold="true" box="[532,547,655,681]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">–</emphasis>
38
</figureCitation>
). Both spermathecae oval, of different size, dark brown, flattened basally; both spermathecae with collars; egg guide relatively wide, 4.5× as long as maximum width, acute apically; middle and ventral part of medial membrane covered with numerous small brown teeth; ventral seminal receptacle, left blade, proctiger and cerci as on 
<figureCitation id="13332A33FFEF483929F2FC8CFE9AB959" box="[211,289,783,810]" captionStart="Figs 30–38" captionStartId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" captionTargetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-306@5.[267,1169,874,1740]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figs 30–38. M. pratensis sp. n., holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">fig. 38.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEF483A29C3FCACFB1EBA99" blockId="5.[174,1233,175,874]" lastBlockId="6.[166,1225,175,682]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">
B i o n o m i c s. One generation was recorded in June. Host plant unknown, but probably the flies are associated with 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEF48392B4AFCD3FC93B91A" box="[619,808,848,874]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jacea">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEF48392B4AFCD3FC93B91A" box="[619,808,848,874]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">Centaurea jacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., as 
<specimenCount id="9D0EFD3FFFEF48392A57FCCCFBA3B919" box="[886,1048,847,874]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
were caught in thicket of this plant in a small meadow, where no other possible host plants were present. Other specimens were collected on motley grass meadows with 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2AB0FF53FBF7BA9A" box="[913,1100,208,234]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jacea">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2AB0FF53FBF7BA9A" box="[913,1100,208,234]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">Centaurea jacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., too.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF77663EFFEF4839299FF95DFD9CBD37" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6449448" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6449448" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6449448/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" startId="5.[190,229,1758,1780]" targetBox="[299,1156,895,1722]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEF4839299FF95DFD9CBD37" blockId="5.[189,1248,1758,1860]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">
Figs 30–38. 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEF48392810F95CFE13BC87" authority="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit, 2016" authorityName="Guglya Results &amp; Melanagromyza &amp; Guglya &amp; e &amp; Head &amp; Orbit" authorityYear="2016" box="[305,424,1759,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEF48392810F95CFE13BC87" box="[305,424,1759,1780]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="412">M. pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24F57DFFFEF4839288FF95DFE5FBC87" box="[430,484,1758,1780]" pageId="5" pageNumber="412" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, holotype: 30, 31 — male head; 32 — phallus, ventral view; 33 — same, lateral view; 34 — male wing; 35 — epandrium-hypandrium complex; 36 — ejaculatory apodeme; paratype (female terminalia): 37 — spermathecae, VII tergit, VII sternit; 38 — ventral seminal receptacle, egg guide, left blade, proctiger and cerci. Scale bar 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A29FAFF6CFB72B819" blockId="6.[166,1225,175,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">
D i a g n o s i s. The new species is superficially similar, in having proclinate and reclinate frorb sta together, wide lunule with slight furrow and white calypter, to 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2D1CFE93FEF9BB39" authority="Hering, 1933" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dettmeri">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2D1CFE93FB73BB5A" box="[1085,1224,271,297]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">M. dettmeri</emphasis>
Hering, 1933
</taxonomicName>
, running to that species in the key by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B47FFEC483A2BD6FEACFC66BB39" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[759,989,303,330]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 416" refId="ref5650" refString="Papp, L., Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Vol. 1. Agromyzinae. Pars Ltd., Nagykovacsi, 1 - 416." type="book chapter" year="2015">Papp, Černý (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, but differing by the orbit slightly projecting above eye only at level of orb s (lateral view); last section of CuA 
<subScript id="178C34F3FFEC483A2D88FEE1FB0ABB03" attach="left" box="[1193,1201,354,368]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">1</subScript>
&gt; 0.75× (0.85×) as long as penultimate; margin yellow; mesonotum and scutellum slightly shining, blackish-grey (dorsal view); abdomen strongly shining, yellowish-green; inner surface of surstylus covered only with numerous short and small spines; setae on cerci short, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D35FFEC483A2859FE53FDB9BB9A" authorityName="Hering" authorityYear="1933" box="[376,514,463,489]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Melanagromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dettmeri">
<emphasis id="B97CEAA4FFEC483A2859FE53FDB9BB9A" box="[376,514,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">M. dettmeri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
orbit projecting as narrow ring above eye (lateral view); last section of CuA 
<subScript id="178C34F3FFEC483A287BFD81FED9B863" attach="left" box="[346,354,514,528]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">1</subScript>
&lt;0.75× (0.67×) as long as penultimate; margin pale brown; mesonotum “matt, faintly greenish or coppery, abdomen distinctly shining, variably coppery-greenish or bluish”; “inner surface of surstylus with group of denser and long setae on ventral margin and group numerous spines on inner surface” (
<bibRefCitation id="EF994B47FFEC483A2BDBFDCCFC6CB819" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[762,983,591,618]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413" pagination="1 - 416" refId="ref5650" refString="Papp, L., Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Vol. 1. Agromyzinae. Pars Ltd., Nagykovacsi, 1 - 416." type="book chapter" year="2015">Papp, Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
); setae on cerci long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB736B6FFEC483A29FAFDECFDBAB8D9" blockId="6.[166,1225,175,682]" pageId="6" pageNumber="413">E t y m o l o g y. The name reflects the locality (a thicket of meadow plants), where all the specimens were collected.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
